// Navbar.js
import React from "react";
import {
  ChakraProvider,
  CSSReset,
  Box,
  Flex,
  Link,
  Spacer,
  Image,
} from "@chakra-ui/react";
import { SettingsIcon } from '@chakra-ui/icons'

const Navbar = () => {
  return (
    <ChakraProvider>
      <CSSReset />
      <Box bg="#0066CC" w="100%" h="110px" display="flex" p={4} margin={"auto"}>
        <Flex align="center">
          <Image
            src="/img/TPRICOn4333.png"
            alt="Logo"
            boxSize="110px"
            objectFit="contain"
            mr={4}
          />
        </Flex>
        <Spacer />
        <Flex align="center" justify="center">
          <Spacer />
          <Link href="#" color="white" mr={4}>            
            <Flex gap={2} align="center" justify="center">
              <Image
                src="/img/usericon.jpg"
                alt="Logo"
                boxSize="40px"
                objectFit="contain"
                style={{ borderRadius: "50%" }}
                mr={2}
              />
              <Box>Username</Box>
            </Flex>
          </Link>
          <Link href="#" color="white" mr={4}>
            TH | EN
          </Link>
          <Link href="#" color="white" mr={4}>
          <SettingsIcon/>
          </Link>
        </Flex>
      </Box>
    </ChakraProvider>
  );
};

export default Navbar;
